</p>
<dl>
<dt>This page is deprecated
</dt>
<dd>These instructions apply to Hyrax version 1.10 and older (BES 3.13.x and earlier)
</dd>
</dl>
<p></font>
</p>
<dl>
<dd><dl>
<dd> <font size="4">For Hyrax 1.11 and newer, please see the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.opendap.org/download/hyrax">Hyrax release page</a> for information about the binary installation or see the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="../index.php/Hyrax_GitHub_Source_Build">github page</a> for information about source builds.</font>
</dd>
</dl>
</dd>
</dl>
<p><br />
The BES comes with a default configuration that is compatible with the default configuration of the OLFS. If you do a default install of each one you should get a running Hyrax server that will be pre-populated with test data suitable for running the integrity tests.
</p><p><br />
</p>
